      "designInstructions": "### Visual Language: Glassmorphism & Depth\n- **Surface Treatment**: Use a mix of deep navy (#011F5B) and space indigo (#1E2952) for backgrounds. Cards should feature glassmorphism (#glassmorphism) with a 12px blur, subtle 10% white borders, and 60% opacity backgrounds to create layering.\n- **Color Accents**: Use Neon Cyan (#00FFFF) for primary progress indicators, success states, and glowing accents. Use Blue Violet (#8A2BE2) for secondary actions and subtle background glows (#gradient-mesh).\n- **Typography Hierarchy**: Use 'Inter' for bold, technical headings and 'DM Sans' for clean, readable body text. Implement uppercase tracking (0.18em) for eyebrow labels to give a professional, engineered look.\n\n### Layout & Spacing\n- **Grid System**: Use a structured sidebar-based layout (#sidebar-dashboard) with a focus on information density without clutter. Implement a balanced spacing rhythm with generous 2rem gaps between main sections.\n- **KPI Floating**: Overlap key metric cards over main content areas (#kpi-overlay) to create a dynamic, modern feel.\n\n### Component Styling\n- **Interactive Elements**: Buttons should have a high-contrast glowing effect (#pulse-glow) on hover. Use 18px size for sidebar icons to ensure visual balance.\n- **Data Visualization**: Charts should be radial (#radial-chart) or feature glowing comparison bars (#comparison-bars) in cyan and violet.\n- **Borders**: Avoid solid flat borders. Use multi-layer shadows (#simple-elevation) or subtle gradient strokes to define card edges.\n\n### Imagery & Iconography\n- **Visual Assets**: Use abstract 3D fluid shapes on dark backgrounds for a futuristic feel. Iconography should be minimal and technical (Tabler Icons).\n- **Animation Cues**: While the canvas is static, the design should imply smooth transitions with clear hover state definitions in the layout.",
      "created": "2026-05-09T12:13:44.545815+00:00",
      "modified": "2026-05-09T12:13:44.545815+00:00"
    },
