      "designInstructions": "### Visual Language: Brutalist Monochrome\n- **Aesthetic**: High-contrast, minimalist, and brutalist. Use absolute black (#000000) and pure white (#FFFFFF).\n- **Surface Treatment**: Replace glassmorphism with solid, clean-edged cards. Use subtle 1px black borders on white backgrounds.\n- **Accents**: No color accents. Use bold typography, thick borders, and solid fills to create hierarchy.\n- **Imagery**: Use grayscale or high-contrast black and white photography. Abstract geometric patterns are preferred over fluid shapes.\n\n### Typography\n- **Hierarchy**: Extremely clear and bold. Large headings should feel like architectural elements.\n- **Tracking**: Tighten tracking for headlines to create a dense, powerful look.\n\n### Layout\n- **Borders**: Use sharp corners (cornerRadius: none) for a professional, Swiss-style industrial feel.\n- **Spacing**: Use \"negative space\" as a design element. Large areas of pure white to separate sections.",
      "created": "2026-05-09T12:16:27.061185+00:00",
      "modified": "2026-05-09T12:16:27.061185+00:00"
